      </tei:opener>

      <tei:p rend="first"><tei:handShift new="#TPbmu"/>The taking-over of the capital of 20 million
        Kronen (2,000 shillings) for the purpose of establishing a "<tei:rs key="entity-000165"
          type="person">Sophie Deutsch</tei:rs> Musician's Stipend Endowment" from the former
          <tei:rs key="entity-002425" type="organization">Association for Feeding of Poor
          Schoolchildren</tei:rs> is duly noted for the granting of approval.<tei:ptr
          corresp="#r0001-fn01" type="footnote"/></tei:p>

      <tei:p rend="first">The administration is consequently requested to draw up, in consultation
        with the professorial college and in agreement with the Finance Procuratoriate of <tei:rs
          key="entity-002484" type="place">Vienna</tei:rs>, an endowment letter, and to submit it
        for the herein-mentioned approval.<tei:ptr corresp="#r0001-fn02" type="footnote"/> In this
        connection, any limitation on the right of award to which Court Counselor Dr. <tei:rs
          key="entity-000632" type="person">Heinrich <tei:hi rend="sperr">Schenker</tei:hi></tei:rs>
        is entitled for his lifetime by way of its being tied to a slate of candidates is to be
        avoided as contrary to the donor's will. Nevertheless, an approach is to be made to the
        named person to determine the manner in which in his opinion the awarding of the stipends
        could be conducted after his death and in the closest conformity with the wishes of the
          <tei:rs key="entity-000165" type="person">testatrix</tei:rs>, and the procedure determined
        for this is to be recorded in the endowment letter.</tei:p>

      <tei:p rend="first"><tei:pb n="2"/>All attachments to the report we do not need here are
        returned herewith enclosed.<tei:ptr corresp="#r0001-fn03" type="footnote"/></tei:p>

